Baringo MCA Nelson Lotela has been reported missing. The Silale ward representative is said to have been abducted by three men at around 5.30pm on Sunday at Nginyang' River in Tiaty sub-county. Three men allegedly roughed up the MCA and bundled him into a saloon car which was being escorted by a Nissan Navara pickup whose registration number had been scrapped off. Baringo County Commissioner Henry Wafula has confirmed the incident, saying that security agencies have been activated to track the missing MCA. More to follow  